    #include &lt;iostream&gt;

    int main()
    {
       HOUSE h; 
       std::cin &gt;&gt; h.room.bed;
    }

And probably not use all CAPITAL names. Some use them for globals, I am more on the side of banning them completely. Names should speak for themself, no need to shout. `House` is clear enough if you use first letter capital for classes and all small letters for instances (eg `house`). Thats also what Stroustrup suggests in [his guideline](http://www.stroustrup.com/Programming/PPP-style.pdf).

